    'subj' => 'Stutterwarp in Traveller',
    'from' => 'HPJKimba@ihc.com',
    'body' => 'The maximum range of stutterwarp drives as described in the 2300 rules is 7.7 light years.  Since one parsec equals 3.26 light-years and 6.72 light years equals two parsecs, the maximum distance a stutterwarp ship can go without discharging is two and a third parsecs (just over Jump 2).  This maximum distance is completely separate from how quickly you traverse the 7.7 light years (which is what your numbers were referring to).
Therefore, I think a stutterwarp would be an interesting variation in a Traveller universe for tramp type ships to wander around on the Mains, but would not be especially useful in going across the rifts (where Jump 6 is just barely enough in some places).
- - Joseph
